When using the mysqli_query function in the procedural style, it requires two parameters. The firs parameter will be the link that you should have created earlier. For instance you will have a statement like the one below:<br />
<div class="code_block">$link = mysqli_connect("localhost", "my_user", "my_password", "world");</div><br />
This establishes the link and stores information in the <em>$link</em> variable, though you may have named it something different.<br />
<br />
In the <em>mysqli_query</em> call you will need to put that in as well as your query. It should look something like this:<br />
<div class="code_block">mysqli_query($link, "SELECT * FROM 'users' WHERE 'username' = '$username'")</div><br />
<br />
Kindest Regards,<br />
Scott M</div>
