				                <div>Hello Shahrin,<br />
<br />
The error tells you where the syntax error is within your query. It states the error begins near 'as, as, as, kjkj, sdf, 30, hgh, Female, hghg, hghg)'. This means your query looks like this:<br />
<div class="code_block">INSERT INTO patient (pName,email,password,contactNo,address,dateOfBirth,city,gender,accountNo,bloodGroup)<br />
VALUES(as, as, as, kjkj, sdf, 30, hgh, Female, hghg, hghg);</div><br />
<br />
Your error falls under the <a href="http://www.inmotionhosting.com/support/website/database-troubleshooting/error-1064#incompatible">Incompatible Types</a> section. Note there are no quotes around the values, this means they are not being entered as string variables, so the code has no idea what to do with them. You will need to rewrite the query to include single quotes around any string variable. Assuming all the fields are strings, the query code will look like this:<br />
<div class="code_block">$sql = "INSERT INTO patient (pName,email,password,contactNo,address,dateOfBirth,city,gender,accountNo,bloodGroup)VALUES ('$PName',' $Email', '$Password', '$ContactNo', '$Address', '$DateOfBirth', '$City', '$Gender', '$AccountNo', '$BloodGroup')" ;</div><br />
<br />
Make sure you do not have quotes around any variables that are numeric or date/time. That should take care of it for you.<br />
<br />
Kindest Regards,<br />
Scott M</div>
